-- Delta Holding of Serbia Posts 6.5% Rise in First-Half Revenue
-- B y   G o r d a n a   F i l i p o v i c
-- 2012-07-25T13:24:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-25/delta-holding-of-serbia-posts-6-5-rise-in-first-half-revenue.html
Delta Holding DOO Beograd ,  Serbia ’s
biggest private-sector employer, reported a 6.5 percent increase
in first half revenue, driven by its insurance, retail and
agribusiness divisions.  The closely held Serbian company posted revenue of 39
billion dinars ($401 million). Earnings before interest, taxes,
depreciation and amortization surged 24 percent to 3.6 billion
dinars, according to a statement on the company’s website.  The company forecast 2012 revenues of 850 million euros ($1
billion), according to the statement.  Delta’s 2011 revenue was 1.42 billion euros, including the
results of Delta Maxi Grupa through July 2011, when the food
retail division was sold to  Delhaize Group SA (DELB)  for 932.5 million
euros in cash and other customary adjustments of 318 million
euros, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gordana Filipovic in Belgrade at 
